====Division One====
{{main|2017 ICC Under-19 Cricket World Cup Asia Qualifier Division One}}
The Asia Division One tournament was played in Singapore from July 2017 to july2017.

Afghanistan and Nepal, teams who played on last Under 19 World Cup will be joined by two finalist of 2016 ICC Under-19 Cricket World Cup Asia Qualifier Division Two, Singapore and Malaysia.Afghanistan win this tournament by win of 6 out of 6game while Nepal win 4 matches out of 6 matches .And Afghanistan was qualified for [[Under-19 Cricket World Cup|2018 u-19 cricket  world cup  held in New Zealand]] .

===East Asia-Pacific===
The East Asia-Pacific regional qualifier will be held in [[Apia]], [[Samoa]], from 8–16 August 2017. Four teams will participate in a double round-robin: [[Fiji national under-19 cricket team|Fiji]], [[Papua New Guinea national under-19 cricket team|Papua New Guinea]], [[Samoa national under-19 cricket team|Samoa]], and [[Vanuatu national under-19 cricket team|Vanuatu]].<ref>[http://cricketpasifika.com/2016/09/29/icc-eap-announces-regional-tournaments-2017-2018/ "Cook Islands excluded from ICC EAP Tournaments"], CricketPasifika, 29 September 2016. Retrieved 8 October 2016.</ref><ref>[https://www.icc-cricket.com/u19-cwc-2018/eap/qualifier-2017/about 2017 EAP Qualifier]</ref>

===Europe===
====Division Two====
